; A $assert inside the `decl` macro must point at the USER's call site (this file),
; not at the assert's location in std/c-interop.sexc.
(defn int main ()
  (decl x 5)
  (return 0))
;==EXPECTED-ERROR==
<stdin>:4:3: error[macro]: decl: binding must be (type name) or (:mods base name)
  (decl x 5)
  ^

Signature: (decl binding init &rest rest)
Doc: Let*-style variable declarations with required initializer.
Example: (decl (int x) 10 (int y) (+ x 5))
